e  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":7,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":52,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Lainham was born about 1330, in Essex, England, his father, Edmund Lenham, was 27 and his mother, Alice, was 27. He married Mrs Robert Lainham. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1330–":"umbes 1330–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1418":"1418","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"about 1330–":"noin 1330–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","about 1330":"noin 1330","1418":"1418","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"about 1330–":"environ 1330–Décédé","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1340–Female":"134